<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  HC career-level statistic. Drives the per-shift Performance bar in the
  expanded Career Panel (PerformanceDetails.as in the Olympus UI).

  HOW IT WIRES UP TO THE UI
  -------------------------
  Every career_level_Adult_Historian_L*.xml references this stat as
  `performance_stat`. The Olympus AS3 panel renders the bar like:

      this.mcProgressBar.SetRange(performanceData.min_value,
                                  performanceData.max_value);
      this.mcProgressBar.SetValue(_loc3_.performance);

  (PerformanceDetails.as:93-94). `performanceData` is a
  `PerformanceStaticData` object whose `.min_value` / `.max_value` are
  populated by the C++ runtime from the Statistic SimData binary referenced
  via `performance_stat` — NOT from the runtime CareerLevel tuning.

  CANONICAL FIELD NAMES (Statistic.INSTANCE_TUNABLES)
  ---------------------------------------------------
  Confirmed by reading `statistic.pyc` from The Sims 4 1.124.55:

      class Statistic.INSTANCE_TUNABLES = (
          'initial_tuning', 'stat_asm_param',
          'min_value_tuning', 'max_value_tuning',
          'stat_name', 'icon',
          'persisted_tuning', 'gallery_load_behavior',
          'apply_value_to_object_cost',
      )

  EA's own adult-career performance stats (e.g. statistic_Career_Performance_Writer
  s="27784", extracted from SimulationFullBuild0.package) use the shape:

      [I c=Statistic i=statistic m=statistics.statistic ...]
        [T n=initial_value]0[/T]            (deprecated shortcut name)
        [T n=max_value_tuning]100[/T]
        [T n=min_value_tuning]-100[/T]
      [/I]

  EA uses the (deprecated but still accepted) shortcut `initial_value` rather
  than the modern `[U n=initial_tuning][T n=_initial_value]...[/T][/U]`
  form. Both shapes are valid in 1.124; we match EA's shape verbatim.

  (Bracket-form above intentional — the s4tk-builder root-tag parser greps for
  the first instance-tag in the file, so an EA-shape example inside this
  comment would shadow the real root tag below.)

  THE BUG THE TWO PREVIOUS AGENTS MISSED
  --------------------------------------
  All the tunable field names were fixed in commit d7428a8 (issue/22), and
  the names ARE correct, BUT THE PACKAGE DID NOT EMIT A SIMDATA COMPANION
  FOR THIS RESOURCE.  EA's runtime reads `performance_stat -> Statistic
  SimData -> min_value_tuning / max_value_tuning` to assemble
  PerformanceStaticData.  With no Statistic SimData in our package, the C++
  shim constructs PerformanceStaticData with min==max==0 and the bar
  throws:

      Error: ProgressBar: Maximum cannot be equal to minimum
          at olympus.gui.progressbars::ProgressBar/SetRange()
          at widgets.Gameplay.SimInfoHUD.CareerPanel::PerformanceDetails/Draw()
          ...

  Layer B now generates a Statistic SimData (3-column row, schema hash
  0x8273c673 — see Build/simdata/src/build/classes/schemas.ts) so the C++
  runtime gets a real min_value_tuning / max_value_tuning pair.

  RANGE CHOICE: -100..+100, matching EVERY EA Career Performance stat
  (Writer, Entertainer, Criminal, Culinary, …).  The 0..5 range used
  pre-d7428a8 was wrong even with a working SimData: each shift contributes
  base_performance=8, missed_work_penalty=35, performance_per_completed_goal=5
  — these tunables saturate a 0..5 range on the first action.

  The 0..5 Karrierestufe counter that historian_career.py.TIERS tracks for
  the Layer A pie-menu flow is a separate concern handled by the L1..L5 loot
  actions (HC_Loot_Add_HistorianLevel_*.xml — those add fixed amounts).  The
  Layer A flow does NOT read this stat's value; only the UI panel does.
-->
<I c="Statistic" i="statistic" m="statistics.statistic" n="HC_Statistic_HistorianLevel" s="TBD_INSTANCE_ID">
  <T n="initial_value">0</T>
  <T n="max_value_tuning">100</T>
  <T n="min_value_tuning">-100</T>
</I>
